
What is an Image Widget?
Simple definition: A widget that displays pictures in your app. It can show images from the internet, your phone's storage, or your project's assets.

Think of it like: An <img> tag in HTML.

The 4 Main Ways to Display Images=========================================================================================================
Constructor          	When to Use	                         Example
Image.network()	      Images from the internet (URL)	     Image.network('https://...')
Image.asset()	        Images in your project folder	       Image.asset('assets/logo.png')
Image.file()        	Images from device storage         	 Image.file(File('/path/to/image'))
Image.memory()	      Images from raw data	               Image.memory(bytes)


The 3 Most Important Properties

1️⃣ width and height (Size)
What it does: Sets the size of the image.

dart
Image.network(
  'https://...',
  width: 200,
  height: 200,
)


2️⃣ fit (How to Fit Inside)
What it does: Controls how the image fits within its box.

Fit Value              	What It Does
BoxFit.cover	          Fill the box, crop if needed (most common)
BoxFit.contain	        Show entire image, may leave empty space
BoxFit.fill	            Stretch to fill box (distorts image)
BoxFit.fitWidth	        Fit to width, clip height
BoxFit.fitHeight        Fit to height, clip width
BoxFit.none           	Keep original size



3️⃣ cacheWidth and cacheHeight (Memory Optimization)
What it does: Decodes the image at a smaller size to save memory.

dart
Image.network(
  'https://...',
  cacheWidth: 200,  // Decode to 200px wide
  cacheHeight: 200, // Decode to 200px tall
)


Why it matters: A 4K image uses 30MB+ of RAM. Resizing it saves memory.




